<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hack 'n' Slash</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">From what I've been reading Mythic and the entire playerbase seem to be going crazy over the idea that someone has access to an overhead map and being able to "cheat" (ideas of just what is a cheat vary, so everything not blessed by Mythic fall into this category). For me, the map is the most important thing of Odin's Eye - I get lost so easily it's not even pathetic (which is why I'm anxiously awaiting a version of OE that doesn't require MDK or RH).<P>I've also read Scott Jennings' (aka Lum the Mad) post on Camelot Herald that they're studying OE in an effort to break it, or at the very least catch the people using it. I'm no techie, heck I've just begun playing around with Linux, but from what I've gleaned from the Internet and friends who do know it, with a box set in passive sniffing mode with internet service routed through it they can't detect OE. Sure they can make it difficult for people like me to use OE, but they can't actually stop it.<P>It seems kind of funny that a company is going to such lengths to break a program that is still in development when their game is not yet even fully implemented. Slap me silly and call me a redhead, but I'd like to be able to play my game as it was PROMISED to me 3 months ago. Trying to stop something that not even Verant, for all its efforts, could permanantly stop is an outrage that the playerbase should be upset about - OE won't be used by more than 1% of the entire game population (say about .05% of the playerbase at any one time). Instead these people are all predicting the end of the gaming world as we know it and threatening dire repercussions and vengeance against the heathens who dared goose beloved Mythic. The rebel in me now wants OE even more.<P>Mythic, if you're reading this, maybe you might want to consider adding some content to the game - I might have less time researching all about OE and learning about Linux if I had more to do in your game.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viron_X</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You are a moron. its an mmorpg and none of them are ever complete on release. granted there is A LOT missing from DAoC but they never promised it would be perfect on release. and overhead maps, just print out some damn maps yourself you lazy crumb-bum</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
